postcontent:
The new SOST round (Special Operations Science and Technology) was designed for the USMC as a supplemental round to the M855 green tip with more desirable terminal characteristics. Designated as MK318 MOD-0 the round was designed as a barrier defeating round with superior penetration and better ballistic stability when shooting through glass car doors and other barriers where other rounds simply bounce off. It was engineered after the Marine Corp identified issues with the M855 round. MK318 utilizes a 62 grain open tip boat tail match bullet with a lead core and reverse copper jacket creating the open tip. Non-Bonded Open Tip Match Bullet Brass cased reloadable. Muzzle velocity: 3000 fps. 20 rounds per box

title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 1873 Lever Action Repeater .22 short - Parts/Project rifle
postcontent:
Winchester Model 1873 .22 Short Rifle that I inherited from my Grandfather. It was purchased by my Great Grandfather when it was brand new and was used as a farm gun on a routine basis. So, this wasn't just a gun that sat around collecting dust. Serial Number is 524753. According to the Winchester website, the serial number shows it was manufactured in 1898. Straight up, this rifle is in rough shape but, it still fires true! In mint condition I know for a fact these are appraised at up to $15,000. However, I know this rifle is far from it and is truely in need of an owner who would apprciate its beauty.

The rifle has a full-octagon barrel and Third Style receiver with integral dust cover rail and dust cover with serrated edges. The barrel has a dovetail mounted sporting style front sight with silver bead and a sporting style rear sight. The barrel, magazine, forearm cap and receiver appear to have had the bluing stripped off and the hammer, lever and crescent buttplate are casehardened. The stock and forearm are straight grain black walnut with a varnish finish. ".22 CAL/SHORT" is stamped in script letters on the bottom of the brass cartridge elevator. The upper receiver tang is roll-stamped "MODEL 1873". The serial number "524753B" is stamped on the lower tang between the lever latch and the tang screw. 
BBL: 22 inch octagon 
Stock: walnut 
Gauge: 22 short 
Finish: It appears that someone has attempted to strip and sand down the finish. IT WASN'T ME, thats for sure! My Grandfather did it!
Condition: Poor to Fair. This rifle was used routinly as a farm rifle for hunting, pest control, and self defense. It has character to say the least. It is missing some of the original parts such as the main springs and screws, and I think the mag tube is not original. It needs work for sure. Plenty to keep you busy. It would be great as a project or as a parts gun. I am firm on the price $750. Rifle sold AS-IN condition.

I will NOT ship this gun till I have cash in my hand thru PayPal or bank certified money order. I can only ship to a FFL address (thats the law). You must pay shipping costs through FedEx or UPS. I will NOT ship overseas. I can meet you here in Ohio within reason if you live here. I had this up for $1500 before and everyone said it was too much.
